<zfin2:page title="ZFIN Author Guide Checklist">
<div><h1>Author Guide Checklist</h1>
<p>Please be sure to address the following items in your manuscripts:

</p><ol>
<li>Are all gene names current and in ZFIN? Please refer to sequence accession numbers and ZDB-GENE IDs for clarity.
</li><li>Do all sequences used for analysis have accession numbers?  If not, submit to GenBank and provide accession numbers in your manuscript.
</li><li>Do all mutations and transgenics have allele/line designations? If not, email the nomenclature coordinator (nomenclature@zfin.org) to obtain them.
</li><li>Have the developmental stages and anatomical structures been identified in each figure?
</li><li>Have sources and catalog numbers been provided for all antibodies and other reagents used?
</li><li>Have the genotypes (all features and their zygosity) and genetic background for fish been clearly described for each figure?
</li></ol>

</div>
</zfin2:page>
